        td Draw
        td The players both turn to directly face each other.
    tr
        td #{Constants[Enums.Actions.SLAM]} succeeds
        td 
            | The target is pushed into one of the 3 hexes directly away from the player. 
            | The winning player chooses which hex the target is pushed into, and 
            | may follow into the vacated hex if they choose to do so. The target 
            | is turned to directly face the hex that was vacated. The winning player 
            | is turned to face the target (if they followed up) or the vacated hex.
    tr
        td #{Constants[Enums.Actions.SLAM]} doubles
        td
            | The target is also knocked down, and must make an 
            a(href="/actions/#{Enums.Actions.ARMORCHECK}") #{Constants[Enums.Actions.ARMORCHECK]} 
            | against the difference in the number of successes between both players'
            | rolls (e.g. If the winning roll was 3 and the target's roll was 1, then 
            | target player makes a 2 dice #{Constants[Enums.Actions.ARMORCHECK]}).
